Create a Standard WhatsApp Channel in Service Cloud

Set up a standard WhatsApp channel to let your support team help customers over WhatsApp. We recommend creating an enhanced channel instead of a standard one, as standard channels are scheduled for retirement in mid-2025.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
This article applies to:	Standard WhatsApp channels

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up WhatsApp channels:	Configure Messaging AND View Setup and Configuration
To create WhatsApp channels:	System Administrator AND Configure Messaging

IMPORTANT Standard WhatsApp channels are scheduled for retirement in mid-2025. To avoid service interruptions, upgrade your standard WhatsApp channels to enhanced channels before July 30, 2025.

When you work with Salesforce to create a standard WhatsApp Messaging channel, Salesforce activates your number for WhatsApp on your behalf or migrates it from your current business service provider.

Go to https://business.facebook.com and log in to your Facebook Business Manager account. Send an email to whatsappenablement@salesforce.com with the required information.
Salesforce org ID—sandbox or production
Facebook Business Manager ID and the name associated with it
The phone number you want to use for WhatsApp
The name and email address for a point of contact to validate ownership of the phone number
The company name you want to show within WhatsApp

When you’re notified that your channel was created, configure its settings and incorporate your WhatsApp number into your Omni-Channel routing logic.

Now, it’s time to customize the user experience for agents and customers who communicate in your WhatsApp channel. See Increase Messaging Productivity.

Considerations for Upgrading or Migrating to Enhanced WhatsApp
